Sentencas: In this work, three processed carbon fuels including activated carbon, carbon black and graphite have been employed to investigate influence of the chemical and physical properties of carbon on the HDCFC performance in different anode atmospheres at 650-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of different carbon fuels on a hybrid direct carbon fuel cell

Sentencas: The results reveal that the electrochemical activity is strongly dependent on crystalline structure, thermal stability and textural properties of carbon fuels.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of different carbon fuels on a hybrid direct carbon fuel cell

Sentencas: The activated carbon samples demonstrate a better performance with a peak power density of 326 mW cm(-2) in CO2 at 750 degrees C, compared to 147 and 59 mW cm(-2) with carbon black and graphite samples, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of different carbon fuels on a hybrid direct carbon fuel cell

Sentencas: Compared to the ohmic resistance, the polarization resistance plays a more dominated role in the cell performance.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of different carbon fuels on a hybrid direct carbon fuel cell

Sentencas: When replacing N-2 by CO2 purge gas, the power density is the strongly temperature dependent due to the Boudouard reaction.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of different carbon fuels on a hybrid direct carbon fuel cell
